
[1]mollify

   MOL'LIFY, v.t. [L. mollio.] To soften; to make soft or tender. Is.1.

   1. To assuage, as pain or irritation.

   2. To appease; to pacify; to calm or quiet.

   3. To qualify; to reduce in harshness or asperity.
